Use these when implementing **fillable PDF export** (`pdf-lib` / server fill): field names match the widgets in the PDF (see `scripts/interactive_sheet_fields_manifest.json` generated by `scripts/export_interactive_sheet_field_manifest.py`). Do not commit the binary PDFs to git unless distribution rights are clear.

If a file is missing on disk, say so; do not invent tables.

## Which book for what

| Need | Prefer |
|------|--------|
| **Boons, Knacks (by Calling), Birthrights, standard Purviews, Signature Purviews in PB** | `SCION_Pandoras_Box_(Revised_Download).pdf` **first** |
| Core chargen spine (Paths, Attributes, Skills, Callings, Origin Mortal tier) | `Scion_Origin_(Revised_Download).pdf` |
| Visitation + Hero tier steps where PB cross-references Hero | `Scion_Hero_(Final_Download).pdf` |
| Demigod + options | `Scion_Demigod_Second_Edition_(Final_Download).pdf`, `Scion_Demigod_Companion_(Final_Download).pdf` |
| God tier | `Scion_God_Second_Edition_(Final_Download).pdf`, `Scion_God_Players_Guide_(Final_Download).pdf` |
| Edges, Saints, Monsters | `Scion_Players_Guide__Saints__Monsters_(Final_Download).pdf` |
| Pantheons, setting, adventures | `Mysteries_of_the_World_*`, `Once_and_Future_*`, `Realms_of_Mystery__Magic_*`, `Rock_Gods_and_Road_Trips_*`, `Scion_-_Titanomachy_*`, `Scion_Masks_of_the_Mythos_*`, `Scion_Mythical_Denizens_*`, `Scion_Wild_Hunt_*`, `TItans_Rising_*`, tasty-bit compilations |
| Scion: Dragon line | `Scion_Dragon_*`, `Scion_Dragon_Companion_*`, `Scion_Dragon_Tasty-Bit_Compilation_*` |
| MCG character sheet / sheet-adjacent | `248484-ScionCC_v3.pdf` (verify against Origin/Hero for conflicts) |
| Expanded weapon lists, gear examples, Divine Armory tag use | `7711-Divine_Armory.pdf`, `7711-Divine_Armory_-_List_of_Weapons.pdf` (verify tag costs against Origin Revised pp. 123–126 when they overlap) |

Use companions and setting books only when the feature explicitly depends on them.

## Process for code changes

1. Identify the **book + section/page** that defines the rule or list before encoding it.
2. In code or UI, cite **book title (short) + page** where helpful (match the style already used in `chargen.py`).
3. Do **not** paste large copyrighted stat blocks or full Boon/Knack text into the repo; paraphrase mechanics for implementation and keep long verbatim quotes out of source.

## PDF access

Agents may use terminal tools (`pdftotext`, etc.) on paths under `/mnt/c/Users/John/Desktop/Scion/books/` when the environment provides them, to extract structure for implementation.
